reviewText: I happen to like George Lopez [anyway], and this silly comedy was 85% off.I realize it didn't win any Academy Awards... but I haven't SEEN many that DID...that I liked.Okay, so it AIN'T "Citizen Kane" or "Ghandi" It was $1.53, WHAT did I have to lose?___________________________________________________________________Update: I just finished watching the movie. I noticed it STILL costs between a pennyand $5 (dependent upon WHERE). I got a great deal, because, occasionally, I check-outwarehouse deals. It wasn't even the cheapest DVD I got. The audio/video was exceptional,and the story was entertaining. The 2009 Nickelodeon movie was presented --- because ofTHAT year --- in anomorphic widescreen (zooming NOT necessary), and "full" [glass picturetube] screen. The special features and previews are, therefor, "window-boxed" so you'llHAVE to ZOOM those unless you WANT black-bars on all four sides of the picture.The picture --- like I mentioned --- for the main-feature presentation is flawless, and,as seen on my 55" widescreen, without fault... looking HD, through my Blu-ray player; Ibought the DVD... the BD is slightly more.Several of the girls appeared inThe Diary of a Wimpy Kid 1, 2 & 3 [Blu-ray]. I have themall, and MY kids are 36 & 40.A bargain for children of ALL ages; I'm 64.
